{"id":"1901.06319","submitter":"Theodore Yoder","authors":"Theodore J. Yoder","title":"Optimal quantum subsystem codes in 2-dimensions","comments":"18 pages, 6 figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A 99, 052333 (2019)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.99.052333","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Given any two classical codes with parameters $[n_1,k,d_1]$ and\n$[n_2,k,d_2]$, we show how to construct a quantum subsystem code in\n2-dimensions with parameters $[[N,K,D]]$ satisfying $N\\le 2n_1n_2$, $K=k$, and\n$D=\\min(d_1,d_2)$. These quantum codes are in the class of generalized\nBacon-Shor codes introduced by Bravyi. We note that constructions of good\nclassical codes can be used to construct quantum codes that saturate Bravyi's\nbound $KD=O(N)$ on the code parameters of 2-dimensional subsystem codes. One of\nthese good constructions uses classical expander codes. This construction has\nthe additional advantage of a linear time quantum decoder based on the\nclassical Sipser-Spielman flip decoder. Finally, while the subsystem codes we\ncreate do not have asymptotic thresholds, we show how they can be gauge-fixed\nto certain hypergraph product codes that do.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Jan 2019 16:14:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Mar 2019 21:37:35 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 22 May 2019 16:48:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-29"}
