e constitutional isomer\n(TIPS-BT1) differing in the placement of TIPS-acetylene side groups suggests\nthat the magnitude of exchange interaction in the correlated triplet manifold\nplays a critical role dictating 1TT yield in the tetracenic systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Jan 2019 16:16:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-21"}
